question.name: What type of events do the caterers provide services?
What information should i have when inquiring about catering?
Can i place catering order in advance?
Can i taste the food before booking?

answer.text: Catering is provided for weddings, engagements, formal dinners, corporate events, birthdays, meetings, babyshowers and occasions of all types and all sizes.
An estimate of the number of guests you planned to invite, date, food type, type of event and the location you are conducting event is helpful. The parameters of your budget are also important.
Yes, you can place orders days or months in advance. Caterers stay on top of all future orders. they usually require at least three days notice for orders during busy times. Please keep in...
Yes, catering vendors are ready to organize a taster for our larger events. Tastings are based on availability of your proposed menu and must be arranged in advanced.
All type of changes like menu, number of guests, etc. This be done at least 3-5 days before the event date.
